The 31st Civil Society Pre-Summit Consultative Meeting on Gender Mainstreaming in the African Union and Member States #GIMAC is calling for the voice of women and young people to be considered by African leaders in the fight against corruption. Recommendations from the meeting will be forwarded to the AU leaders for discussion during their summit in Addis Ababa this week. The summit will be held under the theme: "Winning the Fight against Corruption: A Sustainable Path to Africa's Transformation." Read more. More the Economic Commission for Africa in this BRIEFING.